title.narrative: Nigeria Youth Employment & Social Support Operation

description.narrative: The project development objective is to increase access of the poor and vulnerable, using improved social safety net systems, to youth employment opportunities in all Participating States and to provide Targeted Cash Transfers to the poor, vulnerable and internally displaced people (IDPs) in the North East States.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Governance and Accountability Plan | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and adopt, and cause eachParticipating State to adopt, a governance and accountability plan in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. | DueDate :31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :Procurement | Description :Recipient shall establish a procurement records management system and train the staffof Federal Operations Coordination Unit and National Directorate of Employment in records management. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Procurement | Description :The Recipient shall organize contract administration training for procurement staffof Federal Operations Coordination Unit and stat offices of National Directorate of Employment, with specifications and in a mannersatisfactory to the Association. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, E, 5 | Description :The Recipient shall cause the North East States to ensure that anyarea in which civil works under the Project will be implemented has been cleared of Explosive Remnants of War ... the Recipientshall provide a confirmation, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, that the area which such civil works will beimplemented has been declared safe and clear of Explosive Remnants of War. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, B, 1. | Description :The Recipient shall, not later than two (2) months following theEffective Date appoint third party monitoring agent(s) for the Project under terms of reference, and with qualifications andexperience satisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :21-Oct-2016

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section V, C, 1. | Description :The Recipient shall, no later than two (2) months followingEffectiveness Date prepare and adopt, and cause each NE State to adopt, a governance and accountability plan in form and substancesatisfactory to the Association. | Due Date :21-Oct-2016

Finance Agreement :Third Party Monitoring | Description :The Recipient shall appoint third party monitoring agent(s) for theProject under terms of reference, and with qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association, in accordance with theprovisions of Section III of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement. | Due Date :31-Dec-2014
